---
// src/components/Framework.astro
---

<section class="framework" aria-labelledby="framework-title">
  <div class="framework-container">
    <div class="framework-intro">
      <p class="framework-eyebrow">Adoption framework</p>

      <h2 id="framework-title" class="framework-title">
        Four conditions determine whether AI creates value.
      </h2>

      <p class="framework-lead">
        A model can perform well and still fail in practice. Sustainable value
        depends on how the technology fits the operating environment, how much
        people trust it, whether teams adopt it, and whether outcomes can be
        measured.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="framework-grid">
      <article class="framework-card">
        <span class="framework-number" aria-hidden="true">01</span>

        <h3>Implementation</h3>

        <p>
          The system must fit existing workflows, technical constraints,
          ownership structures, and customer experience priorities rather than
          force a generic process onto the organization.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="framework-card">
        <span class="framework-number" aria-hidden="true">02</span>

        <h3>Trust</h3>

        <p>
          Teams need to understand what the system does, when to rely on it, how
          decisions are governed, and where human judgment remains essential.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="framework-card">
        <span class="framework-number" aria-hidden="true">03</span>

        <h3>Adoption</h3>

        <p>
          New tools must reduce effort, support real work, and fit the behavior
          of frontline teams. Usage is designed into the workflow rather than
          treated as a training problem after launch.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="framework-card">
        <span class="framework-number" aria-hidden="true">04</span>

        <h3>Measurement</h3>

        <p>
          CRM and operational data should show whether the system improves
          customer outcomes, team performance, service quality, retention, or
          another defined business result.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .framework {
    width: 100%;
    padding-block: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background: var(--color-surface-subtle);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .framework-container {
    display: flex;
    width: min(calc(100% - (2 * var(--page-gutter))), var(--container-page));
    margin-inline: auto;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
  }

  .framework-intro {
    display: flex;
    max-width: 50rem;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .framework-eyebrow {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-blue);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.4;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    text-transform: none;
  }

  .framework-title {
    max-width: 17ch;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 1.55rem + 1.8vw, 3.5rem);
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.04;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .framework-lead {
    max-width: 46rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.25rem);
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .framework-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  }

  .framework-card {
    display: flex;
    min-width: 0;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: var(--color-surface-pure);
  }

  .framework-number {
    color: var(--color-blue);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .framework-card h3 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1.15rem + 0.35vw, 1.625rem);
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  }

  .framework-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  @media (max-width: 52rem) {
    .framework-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    .framework {
      padding-block: clamp(3.5rem, 14vw, 5rem);
    }

    .framework-title {
      max-width: 15ch;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 2.75rem);
    }

    .framework-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }

  @media (forced-colors: active) {
    .framework-card {
      border-color: CanvasText;
    }
  }
</style>
